3. Top User Segmentation

Identifies the Top 10 users and compares "Free" vs. "Premium" spending habits.

- SQL:

SELECT 
  user_id,
  user_tier,
  -- We sum the value ONLY if it was a purchase, otherwise we add 0
  ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN event_type = 'purchase' THEN conversion_value ELSE 0 END), 2) AS total_user_spend,
  -- We count EVERY row to see how many times they actually touched the site
  COUNT(*) AS total_interactions,
  -- We can even see their specific purchase count alongside their visits
  COUNTIF(event_type = 'purchase') AS total_purchases
FROM `fluted-box-488519-p3.sql_practice.product_analyst_sql`
GROUP BY user_id, user_tier
ORDER BY total_user_spend DESC
LIMIT 10;

- Answers:

Free users are the top spenders and there are no premium users in the top 15.
If given the right incentive, the top 15 free users can upgrade to a premium membership.
Maybe we can offer a free trial and/or a premium member discount as part of a thank you.

