4. Platform Performance

Compares revenue and traffic across Mobile, Tablet, and Desktop to prioritize UI updates.

- SQL:

SELECT
  device_type,
  ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(COUNTIF(event_type = 'purchase'), COUNT(DISTINCT session_id)) * 100, 2) as conversion_rate,
  ROUND(SUM(session_duration_sec) / 3600, 2) AS total_hours,
  ROUND(SUM(conversion_value), 2) as total_revenue,
  -- This tells you which device earns the most money for every hour spent on it
  ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(conversion_value), (SUM(session_duration_sec) / 3600)), 2) as revenue_per_hour
FROM `fluted-box-488519-p3.sql_practice.product_analyst_sql`
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY revenue_per_hour DESC;

- Answers:

The data does confirm that tablets have the highest conversion rate at 5.11. Followed by mobile at 4.83, then desktop at 4.53.
But 60% of traffic comes from Mobile, while only 10% of traffic comes from tablets. 
